---
import ContentLayout from '../../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Johnny Minor GM Campaign Hub"
  summary="The spoiler-complete source of truth for the flagship campaign: its hidden structure, emotional turns, revelations, and endgame choices."
  eyebrow="Campaign truth"
  audience="gm"
  spoilerLevel="major"
  theme="gm"
  robots="noindex,nofollow"
  gmGate={true}
>
  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Campaign Truth Summary</p>
    <p>
      Johnny's song is fractured. The campaign is not only about saving the Beams, but about
      deciding whether this cycle can be redeemed, interrupted, or allowed to continue by force.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Act Structure</p>
    <h2>Act I: The Chosen of Johnny</h2>
    <p>Gather the ka-tet, establish faith pressure, and seed doubt without paying it off too early.</p>
    <h2>Act II: The Fire and the Flower</h2>
    <p>Rose Creek is the emotional high point. Let the party feel noble before the story starts charging for that feeling.</p>
    <h2>Act III: Shadow on the Beam</h2>
    <p>Place the Todash Game and the Yoko rescue where the group's internal trust is weakest.</p>
    <h2>Act IV: The Final Red</h2>
    <p>Reveal Jah'kaan, position Dusty as hopeful contrast, close the loop with Rook, then force the final choice.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Must Include</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Johnny's dissonance and the fear that prophecy is failing</li>
        <li>Yoko's rescue and murder as irreducible emotional scar tissue</li>
        <li>Kaitlyn's rebellion seed growing slowly, not suddenly</li>
        <li>Lux and Kaitlyn deaths landing as moral fracture, not just plot twist</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Endgame Choice</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Redeem Johnny and keep the song alive at cost</li>
        <li>Slay Johnny to break the cycle cleanly</li>
        <li>Continue the loop knowingly</li>
        <li>Fall to the Red and redefine what victory means</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
